466
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,291
[BOY STUDENT T]
When did you get in here?

467
00:16:38,375 --> 00:16:39,416
Are your guys'
balls still attached?

468
00:16:39,500 --> 00:16:40,541
[BOY STUDENT T]
Worry about yours!

469
00:16:40,625 --> 00:16:41,416
[NENDOU]
'Cause mine feel weird.

470
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,083
Well, obviously they do.

471
00:16:43,166 --> 00:16:45,541
The snake's on your crotch!

472
00:16:47,166 --> 00:16:48,333
[STUDENTS]
Nendou!

473
00:16:48,416 --> 00:16:49,625
[NENDOU]
I'm dead.

474
00:16:49,708 --> 00:16:50,666
[SAIKI]
Calm down.

475
00:16:50,750 --> 00:16:51,750
It didn't bite
through the fabric.

476
00:16:51,833 --> 00:16:52,875
[BOY STUDENT S]
It's coming toward us!

477
00:16:52,958 --> 00:16:54,416
[NARRATOR B]
The power of Clairvoyance!

478
00:16:54,500 --> 00:16:55,750
By crossing his eyes,

479
00:16:55,833 --> 00:16:58,666
Kusuo is able to remotely
view distant locations.

480
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:00,125
[KAIDOU]
Everybody, get down!

481
00:17:00,208 --> 00:17:01,458
I'll take care of this snake!

482
00:17:01,541 --> 00:17:02,958
Kaidou, what're you doing?

483
00:17:03,041 --> 00:17:05,000
All right,
Murder-Dragoram-Snake.

484
00:17:05,083 --> 00:17:07,583
It's time you face me,
the Jet Black Wings!

485
00:17:07,666 --> 00:17:08,666
Let's go!

486
00:17:08,750 --> 00:17:09,666
[BOY STUDENT V]
That's a real pose!

487
00:17:09,750 --> 00:17:10,625
Let's get outta
here while we can!

488
00:17:10,708 --> 00:17:12,000
So we're having a fake superhero

489
00:17:12,083 --> 00:17:13,708
fight a real
poisonous snake now?

490
00:17:13,791 --> 00:17:15,666
[SAIKI] Kaidou may look
confident right now,

491
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:17,625
but he has no idea what to do.

492
00:17:17,708 --> 00:17:19,166
[KAIDOU] Why did I think
I could fight a snake?

493
00:17:19,250 --> 00:17:20,458
I'm so stupid!

494
00:17:20,541 --> 00:17:22,458
[STUDENTS screaming]

495
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:23,916
[screams]

496
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,166
[KAIDOU]
Oh, no, I'm screwed.

497
00:17:25,250 --> 00:17:26,666
I love you, Mommy!

498
00:17:26,750 --> 00:17:27,416
Take this!

499
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:28,666
Judgement Knights of--

500
00:17:28,750 --> 00:17:29,666
[SAIKI]
Sorry, Kaidou.

501
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:31,833
I'll be handling
this part myself.

502
00:17:31,916 --> 00:17:33,750
[KAIDOU]
Thunder!

503
00:17:33,833 --> 00:17:36,500
[SINGING VOICES]
♪ Judgement Knights of... ♪

504
00:17:36,583 --> 00:17:39,375
[STUDENTS cheering]

505
00:17:39,458 --> 00:17:41,041
[SAIKI] I'm sorry I said
you had the body of

506
00:17:41,125 --> 00:17:42,833
an eleventh grader and
the mind of an eighth.

507
00:17:42,916 --> 00:17:44,166
You don't have real powers,

508
00:17:44,250 --> 00:17:45,625
but you certainly
have real courage.

509
00:17:45,708 --> 00:17:47,500
[KAIDOU]
I really do have super powers!

510
00:17:47,583 --> 00:17:49,791
[NARRATOR B] Thus, the Great
Snake Attack came to an end.

511
00:17:49,875 --> 00:17:52,166
I don't care for this new
attitude of yours, Kaidou!

512
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:53,625
You better watch
what you say, teach.

513
00:17:53,708 --> 00:17:55,375
It ain't a pleasant
thing to get blasted

514
00:17:55,458 --> 00:17:56,916
with the "Judgement
Knights of Thunder."

515
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,500
[MALE TEACHER A] That's it.
Go to the principal's office.

516
00:17:58,583 --> 00:18:00,000
[NARRATOR B]
He's gotten more immature!

517
00:18:00,083 --> 00:18:02,500
[SAIKI] I take back
everything I just said.

518
00:18:12,708 --> 00:18:14,041
[NARRATOR B]
Hey, a pretty girl!

519
00:18:14,125 --> 00:18:16,333
There's no one better at
getting people's attention.

520
00:18:16,416 --> 00:18:18,708
[TERUHASHI]
My name is Kokomi Teruhashi.

521
00:18:18,791 --> 00:18:19,958
And not to sound arrogant, 

522
00:18:20,041 --> 00:18:22,416
but I'm an example
of a perfect pretty girl.

523
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:24,333
Again, I'm not
trying to be a jerk.

524
00:18:24,416 --> 00:18:26,000
I'm just stating a fact.

525
00:18:26,083 --> 00:18:27,500
For the most part,
I don't make a habit

526
00:18:27,583 --> 00:18:29,416
of boasting about
my flawless good looks.

527
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:31,125
Hey, you wanna go out
with me sometime?

528
00:18:31,208 --> 00:18:33,416
[TERUHASHI] Now, if I were
your average, pretty girl.

529
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:35,625
How 'bout you go to a
pig farm and kiss one of them?

530
00:18:35,708 --> 00:18:37,458
[TERUHASHI] I'd probably
say something like that.

531
00:18:37,541 --> 00:18:39,000
But I'm perfect.

532
00:18:39,083 --> 00:18:42,541
I'm sorry, but I have
to study for a test tonight.

533
00:18:42,625 --> 00:18:44,000
[giggles]

534
00:18:44,083 --> 00:18:45,416
Oh, good luck!

535
00:18:45,500 --> 00:18:47,250
[TERUHASHI] So, not only
am I beautiful on the outside,

536
00:18:47,333 --> 00:18:48,958
I'm beautiful on the inside.

537
00:18:49,041 --> 00:18:50,583
And you know what
that means, right?

538
00:18:50,666 --> 00:18:53,833
It means I'm invincible.

539
00:18:53,916 --> 00:18:55,166
That guy's in my class.

540
00:18:55,250 --> 00:18:55,875
What's his name?

541
00:18:55,958 --> 00:18:56,500
Sega?

542
00:18:56,583 --> 00:18:57,166
Sakè.

543
00:18:57,250 --> 00:18:57,750
Saiki!

544
00:18:57,833 --> 00:18:59,041
Kunio Saiki!

545
00:18:59,125 --> 00:19:01,541
Aw, he looks so alone.

546
00:19:01,625 --> 00:19:02,708
Poor thing.

547
00:19:02,791 --> 00:19:05,041
I should go say hi
and brighten his day.

548
00:19:05,125 --> 00:19:06,083
Remember?

549
00:19:06,166 --> 00:19:07,375
I'm not just pretty
on the outside,

550
00:19:07,458 --> 00:19:10,333
I'm also perfectly
pretty on the inside!

551
00:19:10,416 --> 00:19:11,666
[TERUHASHI]
Saiki! Hi!

552
00:19:11,750 --> 00:19:13,791
I couldn't help but
notice you looked sad!

553
00:19:13,875 --> 00:19:15,500
[TERUHASHI] Perfect!
Now he has a memory of me

554
00:19:15,583 --> 00:19:17,125
to cherish for
the rest of his life.

555
00:19:17,208 --> 00:19:18,916
Not only did you
get to be seen talking

556
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,958
to the prettiest girl in
school while out in public,

557
00:19:21,041 --> 00:19:23,416
she's the one who
rushed over to you!

558
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:25,666
I bet you've fallen in love.
That's okay.

559
00:19:25,750 --> 00:19:27,375
Even though we're on
separate social levels,

560
00:19:27,458 --> 00:19:29,541
it's a natural response
to my beauty.

561
00:19:29,625 --> 00:19:32,666
How else are you supposed
to react to perfection?

562
00:19:33,875 --> 00:19:35,333
[TERUHASHI]
That's it?

563
00:19:35,416 --> 00:19:37,041
You're supposed to panic at the
mere thought of touching me!

564
00:19:37,125 --> 00:19:38,375
Oh, I get it!

565
00:19:38,458 --> 00:19:39,750
He's uncomfortable showing
his emotions in public.

566
00:19:39,833 --> 00:19:42,666
That's the only way to
explain his non-reaction.

567
00:19:42,750 --> 00:19:44,583
I bet he's just beating
himself up for being

568
00:19:44,666 --> 00:19:46,333
so bashful around me.

569
00:19:46,416 --> 00:19:49,041
Okay, then, shy guy.
I'll give you another chance.

570
00:19:49,125 --> 00:19:51,083
Because I'm not
just beautiful, I'm nice!

571
00:19:51,166 --> 00:19:52,833
I'm the perfect pretty girl!

572
00:19:52,916 --> 00:19:54,291
Saiki! Silly!

573
00:19:54,375 --> 00:19:56,291
You know it's not polite
to ignore a girl--

574
00:19:56,375 --> 00:19:58,333
[TERUHASHI] He didn't
even stop, let alone bow!

575
00:19:58,416 --> 00:20:00,875
Am I invisible? Am I dead?

576
00:20:00,958 --> 00:20:02,416
Oh! I know!

577
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:04,041
He's so used to being
alone and miserable,

578
00:20:04,125 --> 00:20:05,541
he's probably convinced himself

579
00:20:05,625 --> 00:20:08,291
that any pretty girls who talk
to him are just illusions.

580
00:20:08,375 --> 00:20:10,458
Well! I'm gonna have
to prove to him I'm real

581
00:20:10,541 --> 00:20:13,500
and give him the
happiest day of his life.

582
00:20:13,583 --> 00:20:15,750
[TERUHASHI]
Saiki! Don't leave me alone!

583
00:20:17,458 --> 00:20:18,458
[TERUHASHI]
He dodged?

584
00:20:18,541 --> 00:20:19,541
But if he thinks
I'm an illusion,

585
00:20:19,625 --> 00:20:21,916
why would he have
to step around me?

586
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:23,541
Is it possible
that he's so in love,

587
00:20:23,625 --> 00:20:25,666
even touching my illusion
would be too much?

588
00:20:25,750 --> 00:20:27,208
Even though she's a figment...

589
00:20:27,291 --> 00:20:29,000
[TERUHASHI] It's very flattering
to know that I mean so much

590
00:20:29,083 --> 00:20:31,041
to this poor, pathetic boy.

591
00:20:31,125 --> 00:20:32,375
[SAIKI]
Oh, brother.

592
00:20:32,458 --> 00:20:33,958
Why does this chick from
school keep following me?

593
00:20:34,041 --> 00:20:36,458
Saiki! Hi!

594
00:20:36,541 --> 00:20:37,750
[SAIKI]
Here she comes.

595
00:20:37,833 --> 00:20:39,375
The one thing this
arrogant girl won't consider

596
00:20:39,458 --> 00:20:40,708
is that I'm ignoring her.

597
00:20:40,791 --> 00:20:41,875
Though, to be fair,

598
00:20:41,958 --> 00:20:43,291
if I was the kinda
guy she thinks I am...

599
00:20:43,375 --> 00:20:45,375
Oh, wow, it's Teruhashi!

600
00:20:45,458 --> 00:20:47,375
[SAIKI] ...I probably
would be just like that.

601
00:20:47,458 --> 00:20:48,083
Nendou, too.

602
00:20:48,166 --> 00:20:49,500
Oh, wow, it's Teruhashi!

603
00:20:49,583 --> 00:20:50,375
[SAIKI]
She is very pretty.

604
00:20:50,458 --> 00:20:52,000
In fact, everything Teruhashi

605
00:20:52,083 --> 00:20:53,875
thinks about herself
is actually true.

606
00:20:53,958 --> 00:20:55,458
That's what makes
her so dangerous.

607
00:20:55,541 --> 00:20:57,166
She really does
attract attention.

608
00:20:57,250 --> 00:20:58,583
And because
I don't like attention,

609
00:20:58,666 --> 00:21:00,291
I don't want her around me.

610
00:21:00,375 --> 00:21:01,833
Do you mind if I
tag along with you?

611
00:21:01,916 --> 00:21:04,041
I promise it'll be fun, Saiki!

612
00:21:04,125 --> 00:21:05,333
[SAIKI]
Nendou!

613
00:21:05,416 --> 00:21:06,875
This is bad.

614
00:21:06,958 --> 00:21:08,333
She thinks I think she's fake,
but if he acknowledges her, 

615
00:21:08,416 --> 00:21:09,583
--I have no choice but to
--Hey, buddy,

616
00:21:09,666 --> 00:21:10,916
--acknowledge her, too.
--and girl from school.

617
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:12,833
[SAIKI] I'll be checkmated
by social convention.

618
00:21:12,916 --> 00:21:14,666
Oh wow! I didn't
know you were there!

619
00:21:14,750 --> 00:21:16,375
[SAIKI]
I simply can't let that happen.

620
00:21:16,458 --> 00:21:18,083
I'll disappear into the crowd.

621
00:21:18,166 --> 00:21:20,041
Huh. He didn't see me.

622
00:21:20,125 --> 00:21:21,500
That was a close--

623
00:21:21,583 --> 00:21:23,666
[NENDOU] Hmm? I could swear
I just saw my best friend.

624
00:21:23,750 --> 00:21:24,500
[TERUHASHI]
Huh?

625
00:21:24,583 --> 00:21:26,208
Oh, no! Where did Saiki go?

626
00:21:26,291 --> 00:21:27,458
Huh?! What's going on?

627
00:21:27,541 --> 00:21:29,791
[SAIKI] Whoopsie.
I accidentally teleported.

628
00:21:29,875 --> 00:21:31,416
[TERUHASHI]
Saiki!

629
00:21:31,500 --> 00:21:33,208
[SAIKI] The people around
me didn't seem to notice

630
00:21:33,291 --> 00:21:34,500
my vanishing, but of course

631
00:21:34,583 --> 00:21:36,416
Teruhashi knows
something is off.

632
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:39,500
Well, maybe it's best if
you think I was the illusion.

633
00:21:39,583 --> 00:21:40,875
[TERUHASHI]
Nendou?

634
00:21:42,375 --> 00:21:44,500
Oh, wow! Hey there, Teruhashi!

635
00:21:44,583 --> 00:21:45,625
[TERUHASHI]
Do you know where Saiki went?

636
00:21:45,708 --> 00:21:47,375
What? Buddy? Nope.

637
00:21:47,458 --> 00:21:48,541
Haven't seen 'im.

638
00:21:48,625 --> 00:21:49,875
[TERUHASHI]
It's... like he disappeared?

639
00:21:49,958 --> 00:21:53,250
Is it possible he was a
figment of my imagination?

640
00:21:53,333 --> 00:21:56,000
You're so much in love with me
that you see illusions of me?

641
00:21:56,083 --> 00:21:58,375
Oh, my gosh. No. It can't be.

642
00:21:58,458 --> 00:22:00,000
Don't tell me that I'm... 

643
00:22:00,083 --> 00:22:03,083
Wh-What're these
feelings coming over me?

644
00:22:03,166 --> 00:22:07,833
I think I'm falling
in love... with Saiki?

645
00:22:07,916 --> 00:22:09,958
[SAIKI]
Oh, wow.

646
00:22:10,041 --> 00:22:11,708
Teruhashi.

647
00:23:42,208 --> 00:23:44,250
[SAIKI] Because it's critical
to your enjoying the show,

648
00:23:44,333 --> 00:23:46,833
I'll remind you again that
my name is Kusuo Saiki,

649
00:23:46,916 --> 00:23:50,500
and I'm a psychic with all
sorts of crazy mental powers.

650
00:23:50,583 --> 00:23:52,041
This is annoying.

651
00:23:52,125 --> 00:23:54,500
This season, on <i>The Disastrous</i>
<i>Life of Saiki K.</i> :

652
00:23:54,583 --> 00:23:56,958
Each chapter of the
manga gets an episode!

